    pearls: ["Endometriosis affects approximately 10% of reproductive-age women and is the leading cause of chronic pelvic pain in this population","Average delay from symptom onset to diagnosis is 7-10 years — maintain high clinical suspicion for cyclical pelvic pain","Endometriomas (chocolate cysts) are ovarian cysts filled with old blood from ectopic endometrial tissue; they appear as homogeneous hypoechoic masses on ultrasound","GnRH agonist therapy causes an initial flare (worsening symptoms for 1-2 weeks) before suppression occurs — warn patients about this","Endometriosis staging (revised ASRM classification I-IV) does NOT correlate well with pain severity — minimal disease can cause severe pain","NSAIDs are most effective when started 1-2 days before expected menses onset, not after pain begins"],
